                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.124/271.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 172.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-12-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 20, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that Colonel Gorgas,
                    accompanied by Major Noble and Mr. McGuigan, Secretary of the Commission,
                    arrived at Quito December 15 for the purpose of paying their respects to
                    President Plaza and other members of the Government. The Minister for Foreign
                    Affairs gave a luncheon in honor of the Commission, which left for Guayaquil
                    December 18.</p>
                <p>So far the visit of the Sanitary Commission to Ecuador has been a most pleasant
                    one in every respect.</p>
                <p>I am informed that the Commission will return to Panama on the steamer sailing
                    from Guayaquil December 21.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rutherfurd Bingham.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
